Germany’s Bruederle Says Income Tax Cut Is Needed, Focus Reports

-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 
2011-03-27T11:46:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/germany-s-bruederle-says-income-tax-cut-is-needed-focus-reports.html
German Economy Minister Rainer Bruederle says cuts in the country’s income taxes are necessary
as levies are too high compared with other countries,  Focus 
magazine reported today, citing the minister.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 